news.title: Bolstered infrastructure investment-a catalyst for a $5 trillion economy: Niranjan Hiranandani
news.para: Last-mile connectivity with multi-transit corridors and infrastructure investments will open up vast hinterlands for future real estate developments.

news.title: UK house prices fall more than expected in January 2023: Nationwide
news.para: January's decline in house prices was the fourth drop in a row - the longest unbroken run of declines since 2009 - and the fall was twice the size expected in a Reuters poll of economists, adding to signs that the market is slowing rapidly.

news.title: Real Estate Budget 2023: Double non-taxation on REITs finally addressed
news.para: From April 1, 2024 all distribution by a REIT/InvIT representing repayment of debt is taxable as "other income" in the hands of the unit holders.

news.title: Real estate companies' stocks plunge 4% post budget 2023
news.para: Shares of Sunteck Realty plummeted 5.67 per cent to close at Rs 345 per share on the NSE, while Indiabulls Real Estate tumbled 3.81 per cent to end at Rs 69.50 apiece.

news.title: Budget 2023: Rs 19,518 crore allocated to metro projects across India
news.para: The allocation in 2022-23 was Rs 19,130 crore. However, the revised budget estimates for the same for 2022-23 was 15,628 crore, according to budget documents.

news.title: Sebi orders attachment of bank, demat accounts of Subrata Roy, others
news.para: The recovery proceedings have been initiated against these four persons to recover Rs 6.48 crore, which includes all costs, interests, charges and expenses etc, the Securities and Exchange Board of India (Sebi) said in the attachment order.

news.title: Deemed conveyance for new cooperative housing societies gets 'dismal' response in Maharashtra
news.para: Conveyance is the ownership right to the building and the plot on which the structure is built. Deemed conveyance is obtained through the competent authority if the developer does not give it.

news.title: Gurugram: DTCP serves notices to 70 over commercial activities on residential plots
news.para: The department has served show cause notices to these property owners and sought their replies in a week on the complaints.

news.title: A balance budget with some hits and some misses, says real estate industry stakeholders
news.para: From the real estate industry's point of view, there were no major direct announcements in the Union Budget 2023. However, industry stakeholders are still calling it a balanced budget which will help push country's economy in the right direction.

news.title: What real estate industry gained from Budget 2023
news.para: Real estate industry received some push from the Union Budget 2023. Finance minister Nirmala Sitharaman announced some key initiatives and schemes in the budget that are expected to benefit real estate industry. Take a look!

news.title: Public sand mining sites to be declared in Punjab: Mining minister
news.para: Mining and geology minister Gurmeet Singh Meet Hayer said on Monday that the public mining sites will help in checking any malpractice to jack up the prices of sand and give the freedom of choice to people to buy sand from the source of choice and at price of choice.

news.title: Chhattisgarh consumer forum asks Sunita Developers to pay compensation to flat buyer
news.para: Complanint Sanjana Agrawal, a resident of Durg, had entered into an agreement with Sunita Developers in 2014 to buy a flat on the fourth floor of the multi-storey Sunita Park Phase-1 project and made the payment of Rs 57,75,729. In addition, the builder took Rs 3,00,000 for providing parking and other facilities.

news.title: Builder arrested for defrauding 200 flat buyers in Lucknow
news.para: The accused identified as Pankaj Thakur was arrested from his office. SHO, Vibhutikhand, Ram Singh, said Pankaj was working along with one Shashank Gupta and had floated a firm which used to promise flats, houses.

news.title: Madhya Pradesh HC orders Bhopal collector to recover RERA fine or face action
news.para: The petitioner Sanjay Sahai, a Bhopal based professor, pleaded he had bought 2400 square feet land from a builder in 2011 for Rs 8.40 lakh. Sahai paid the builder Rs 6.40 lakh but work on project didn't start till 2014.

news.title: Budget 2023 real estate: Builders expects deduction in home loans rates
news.para: Real estate industry experts say there should be some tax concessions for first-time homebuyers and re-introducing GST with an input tax credit for under-construction properties that will generate demand among homebuyers.
